      "From his reading, including a heavily annotated copy of Marco Polo's travels, Columbus developed a fixed and audacious conviction. He believed the globe was small enough that a ship could reach the wealthy spice lands of Asia by sailing west across the open ocean, rather than making the long and dangerous journey east around Africa. His estimate of the distance was badly wrong, far too short, but it gave him the confidence to try.",
