      "Many of his inventions could never have been built with the materials and power sources of his day, and most of his notebooks lay unread for hundreds of years, so his direct influence on technology was limited. But as an emblem of human possibility he is unsurpassed. Leonardo da Vinci stands as the eternal archetype of the curious mind that refuses to specialise, the builder who unites art, science and engineering into a single relentless drive to understand and create.",
