      "In wrestling with these equations Cardano became one of the first mathematicians to take seriously the square roots of negative numbers, the quantities we now call imaginary numbers. He found them puzzling and even disturbing, but he did not flinch from them, opening a door that would lead, centuries later, to complex numbers, a tool indispensable to modern physics and engineering.",
      "His gambling, meanwhile, led him to think systematically about chance. He wrote a book on games of dice that contained the first methodical analysis of probability, anticipating by nearly a century the formal theory of probability developed by Pascal and Fermat.",
      "Cardano was also an inventor of mechanisms. He described and popularised the gimbal, a set of nested rings pivoting on different axes so that an object mounted at the center stays level no matter how its support tilts or turns. Known as the Cardan suspension, the same principle keeps a ship's compass steady, stabilises cameras, and orients instruments aboard spacecraft, a five hundred year old idea still spinning quietly inside modern technology.",
