      "Evangelista Torricelli was a brilliant young Italian mathematician and physicist who came of age just as the scientific revolution that Galileo had launched was gathering force. Orphaned early and educated by his uncle, a monk, he showed such mathematical gifts that his work was sent to the aging Galileo himself.",
      "Galileo was so impressed that he invited Torricelli to Florence, where the young man served as his secretary and assistant during the great astronomer's final months under house arrest. When Galileo died in 1642, Torricelli succeeded him as mathematician and philosopher to the Grand Duke of Tuscany, inheriting the mantle of Italy's leading scientist.",
