      "His reputation grew so great that King Louis XIV of France invited him to Paris to lead the newly founded Royal Observatory. Cassini accepted, eventually became a French citizen, and made the observatory into the foremost center of astronomy in the world, founding a dynasty of astronomers who would direct it for four generations.",
