      "Three centuries after his death, his legacy returned dramatically to the sky. In 1997 the space agencies of the world launched a great robotic probe to Saturn and named it Cassini. For thirteen years it orbited the planet, sending back breathtaking images of the very rings, gaps and moons that Giovanni Domenico Cassini had first glimpsed by eye through his telescope in Paris.",
