      "Over a career spanning some seventy years he produced more than a thousand instruments, violins above all, but also violas, cellos, guitars and harps. He worked with relentless attention to every detail: the choice and aging of the wood, the precise carving and arching of the front and back plates, the placement of the sound holes, and the secret recipe of his glowing varnish.",
