      "Under his leadership Olivetti grew from a typewriter maker into one of the most admired technology and design companies in the world. But what set Adriano apart was a conviction that ran against the grain of his era: that a factory had profound responsibilities beyond simply making money, and that industry should serve human beings and the wider community, not the other way around.",
