      "He drove the company boldly into the new world of electronics and computing. Out of that investment came the Programma 101, released in 1965, a few years after Adriano's sudden death. Compact enough to sit on a desk and usable by a single person, it is widely regarded as one of the first desktop personal computers, a genuine ancestor of the machines we use today.",
      "Adriano Olivetti died in 1960, but his vision has only grown more relevant. He demonstrated, in practice and at scale, that a company could pursue cutting edge technology, beautiful design and the dignity and wellbeing of its people all at once. In an age increasingly concerned with whether technology truly serves humanity, his example reads as a strikingly modern blueprint for the purpose driven builder.",
