      "He led one of the huge experimental teams that built a detector to watch these collisions. In 1983 the gamble paid off spectacularly. Rubbia's team detected first the W and then the Z bosons, exactly as the theory had predicted, a triumphant confirmation of the electroweak theory at the very heart of the Standard Model of particle physics, our best description of the fundamental forces and particles of nature.",
